Turing Test and CAPTCHA — Architecture Design : 

Turing Test: A test to tell man and machine apart. A human judge tries to differentiate and identify corrrectly which is which through a series of 
quesitons answered simultaneously by a human and a machine. If the judge cannot reliably distunguish then the AI is sai to pass the Turing Test.
->Implementation : 

Goal : Determine whether the interacting entity is human or AI.

Architecture : 
        +--------------------+
        |   Human Judge      |
        +---------+----------+
                  |
                  v
         +------------------+
         | Conversation     |
         | Interface (Chat) |
         +---------+--------+
                   |
          +--------+--------+
          |                 |
          v                 v
   +-------------+   +--------------+
   | Human User  |   | AI Agent     |
   +-------------+   +--------------+

Judge does not know which is which

Components :
-User Interface
-Chat interface.
-Conversation Manager
-Routes messages to participants.
-AI Agent and Human participant : Generates responses.
-Judge Module : Evaluates responses and decides.

 CAPTCHA : Completely Automated Public Turing Test to tell Computers and Humans Apart
-> Implementation : 
Goal : Differentiate humans vs bots.

Architecture : 
       +-------------------+
       |   User Request    |
       +---------+---------+
                 |
                 v
        +------------------+
        | CAPTCHA Generator|
        +--------+---------+
                 |
          Image / Puzzle
                 |
                 v
          +--------------+
          |  User Input  |
          +------+-------+
                 |
                 v
        +-------------------+
        | Verification Unit |
        +---------+---------+
                  |
        +---------+----------+
        |                    |
      Human               Bot Blocked

Components : 
->CAPTCHA generator
->distorted text / image recognition / puzzles.
->Challenge delivery module
->Response collector
->Verification module

Workflow : 
1.User accesses website.
2.CAPTCHA challenge generated.
3.User solves challenge.
4.System verifies answer.
5.If correct → allow access.
